Our certificate of incorporation authorizes us to issue up to 1.0 million&#32;shares of preferred stock with designations, rights and preferences determined from time-to-time by our board of directors. Accordingly, our board of directors is empowered, without stockholder approval, to issue preferred stock with dividend, liquidation, conversion, voting or other rights superior to those of holders of our common stock. For example, an issuance of shares of preferred stock could:&#160;&#8226;adversely affect the voting power of the holders of our common stock;&#8226;make it more difficult for a third-party to gain control of us;&#8226;discourage bids for our common stock at a premium;&#8226;limit or eliminate any payments that the holders of our common stock could expect to receive upon our liquidation; or&#8226;otherwise adversely affect the market price of our common stock.We may in the future issue shares of authorized preferred stock at any time.26Table of Contents
